 <br>
One player found a bug that allowed him to group in the same group as a good PC was,and the result was my massive displeasure at the thought of a Teir'dal willingly fighting alongside a dirt-grubbing worshipper of Brell.<br>
 <br>
The guild dealt with it rapidly,but I understand the player wanted exp over roleplaying. Evil isn't always the most social bunch in Norrath(duh!) so some people are simply try anything they can to advance rather than do it the &quot;hard way&quot;-ie by acting in an RP manner. I wonder why these people play here,but I know some folk did come here for reasons other than RPing a character.<br>
 <br>
As I've already lost at least one friend on this server from RP frustration,I don't want to see another drop by the wayside.<br>
 <br>
(Which means if you're around the low 20's and you see me on-find a way to get to near Freeport and you WILL find someone wicked enough to terrorize places with you,naturally. :P)<br>
 <br>
As to reasons to ally with a neutral when you're evil? Some people simply aren't picky-others simply want a particular class in their group so badly that it doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
-Morgrist Vanadil (League of Shadows)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhaelofthevoid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhael of the Void</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/3/01 7:24:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplay vs. social behavior.</span><hr size=1> Do not leave the server because of this, that would be a mistaque.  I too have noticed this, and it buggs me.  My way of dealing with this is by leading by example.  As an officer in my guild, many look to me as an example of how to act.  I have no issue having a little ooc talk with guildies, but that is done in tells, and on rare occasions /g.  Any time we /say anyting, its incharacter.  If some one asks me for &quot;plat plz&quot; or says &quot;wts lammy,50plat&quot; I role play with them.  Most people who came to this server, came to roleplay, and got distracted by the game. often times all it takes to get them back into the mood , is to start them up by role playing your self!  If all else fails , don't group with them, don't interact with them, they'll figure it out and either role play with you, or leave you alone.<br>
<br>
Sorry that's alittle long, but that's how I feel.  Stay with us, roleplay with others on the server, many times you'll be suprised at how they react!  If you're looking for a group to role play with, and see a member of the Indigo Void in the zone, send us a tell.<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
<br>
Rhael of the Void <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/3/01 10:22:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplay vs. social behavior.</span><hr size=1> Well I do see the time for ooc.  I am not blind to think that you can stay in character all the time.  As a guild leader there is no way I can stay completely in character as I have about 10-20 people talking to me at once while I am getting ready to head out to group when I find someone needs some jewelry and I have to go back.  It is very hard to stay in character what bothers me is when people go ooc for no good reason.  I am currently in the middle of the Illusion: Iksar quest and was told to bring a ranger with me or a druid.  As my character does not really accept those I felt that even though it might take me having to stay in Swamp of No Hope for a good 2-5 days trying to get a ton warrior totem.  (Thanks to all the people that have helped me  I am still hunting the Ton <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  /cheer League).  I actually got a tell from a friend guild telling me that my guild was guilding with a neutral from of all places a 1FoL.  They asked if we allowed grouping with pales.  I said I left it up to the people in the guild to roleplay it and when I asked the people they talked about having a rp reason which is where the quote came from.  It is easy to slip into ooc for a second to get an added bonus.  When I sell my jewelry I am open to anyone but if my character does not like you or you are a goodie I usually charge 2-5x the normal price.  I guess I try to imitate the faction/cha that normal vendors use. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/3/01 10:27:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplay vs. social behavior.</span><hr size=1> Hmm..<br>
Roleplay by alignment is kinda hard to do In general if I'm going to get into a pick up group I check that all the questionable races can be hit with spells, and I don't group with racial enemies. That still leaves allot of ground to be covered. Roleplay is preferred, here and I prefer to do it ,but if I'm oom or going divine and the place is tense . I'd get you killed before I got the information out. I'll use the standard shortened version.<br>
<br>
The way I see it is I'm not the roleplay &quot;police&quot; I'm just on this server because I like to roleplay. If someone wants to be a d0Od then they can be I won't get worked up about it, I'll ignore them and they usually leave. Sometimes game information over writes my want to roleplay. But we are on this server to have fun. Lets do that if you want to be the police and see X person doesn't roleplay. Blah, Blah, Blah they just got the mention and acknowledgement they wanted.<br>
<br>
That's my 2 pennies not that they are worth anything<br>
